The paper discusses the security management challenges posed by malicious cyberattacks on online social networks, specifically Facebook discussion groups. This topic falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of predictive models to identify likely targets for such attacks, which involves analyzing the temporal evolution of posts and threads. This could fall under the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper touches on the potential impact of such attacks on political dialogue, which could fall under the sub-category of Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC).
